Package Entities

Class User

java.lang.Object
Entities.User
Direct Known Subclasses:
Student, Supervisor
public class User extends Object
Represents a User in the FYP Management System. A User can only be classified with 1 User Type, that is either Student, Faculty, or FYP Coordinator
Since:
2023-04-14
Version:
1.0
Author:
Lab A34 Assignment Team 1

    • authenticateUser

      public UserType authenticateUser(String userID, String password, ArrayList<Supervisor> supervisorList, ArrayList<Student> studentList, ArrayList<FYPCoordinator> fypCoordinatorsList)
      Authenticates the User trying to log into FYPMS. Verifies and identifies what type of User is trying to log in so as to classify them.
      Parameters:
      userID - Provided UserID Input
      password - Provided Password Input
      supervisorList - ArrayList of Registered Supervisors in FYPMS
      studentList - ArrayList of Registered Students in FYPMS
      fypCoordinatorsList - ArrayList of FYP Coordinators in FYPMS {Usually 1 for every course}
      Returns:
      the UserType Enumeration to identify if it is a valid user.

    • changeUserPassword

      public Boolean changeUserPassword(User loggedUser, Scanner scObject, Console terminalConsole)
      Provides an interface for User to change their Password. Users must verify their identity by providing their password and any password input is masked for security reasons.
      Parameters:
      loggedUser - Logged User
      scObject - Scanner to read input from User
      terminalConsole - Console to mask the Password of User
      Returns:
      a Boolean to inform us if the provided password is correct.
